[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA critical security vulnerability has been detected in Apache PDFBox's OCR [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctionality. The issue is an OS Command Injection vulnerability [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mcom.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that occurs when the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mOCRStreamEngine executes operating system commands with potentially [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattacker-controlled data. This vulnerability could lead to remote code execution if[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexploited.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe issue represents a critical OS Command Injection vulnerability discovered [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthrough fuzzing. This type of vulnerability occurs when an application constructs [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand executes operating system commands using data that may be controlled or [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minfluenced by an attacker, without proper validation or sanitization.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability was detected by Jazzer's sanitizer specifically designed to [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentify OS command injection attacks. The stack trace shows the execution flow [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mleading to the vulnerability:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The entry point is through `[0m[1;35mOCRStreamEngine.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, which is the public API [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethod being called[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. The execution flows through `[0m[1;35mwriteText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → `[0m[1;35mprocessPages[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → `[0m[1;35mprocessPage[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` →[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mrunTesseract[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. The vulnerability is triggered in `[0m[1;35mdoOCR[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method at line [0m[1;36m190[0m[39m of [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mOCRStreamEngine.java[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. This method calls `[0m[1;35mProcessBuilder.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, which is where the actual OS command[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexecution occurs[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. The Jazzer sanitizer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`OsCommandInjection.processImplStartHook`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m intercepts this[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcall and detects that attacker-controlled data is being used in the command[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe key observation is that the OCRStreamEngine is executing Tesseract [0m[1;39m([0m[39man OCR [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mengine[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m as an external process, and some part of the command construction or [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marguments being passed to ProcessBuilder appears to incorporate data that could be [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmanipulated through the PDF input being processed.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo gain a holistic understanding of this vulnerability, the following parts of the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodebase should be investigated:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **[0m[1;35mOCRStreamEngine.doOCR[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m190[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: The exact location where ProcessBuilder [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis instantiated and the command is constructed[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **[0m[1;35mOCRStreamEngine.runTesseract[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m165[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: The method that prepares and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minitiates the Tesseract execution[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **[0m[1;35mOCRStreamEngine.processPage[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m150[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: To understand what PDF page data [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis being processed and passed down[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **[0m[1;35mOCRStreamEngine.processPages[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m140[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: To see how multiple pages are [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandled[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **[0m[1;35mOCRStreamEngine.writeText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m** and **[0m[1;35mOCRStreamEngine.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: The public [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAPI surface that accepts input[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy for OS Command Injection Vulnerability in OCRStreamEngine[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability stems from using PDF custom metadata [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`tesseract-path`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m directly [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mas an executable path in `[0m[1;35mProcessBuilder.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` without any validation. The data [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mflow is:[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**PDF Metadata → `actualTessPath` → ProcessBuilder → OS Command Execution**[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe code at lines [0m[1;36m158[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m159[0m[39m of OCRStreamEngine.java retrieves potentially [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattacker-controlled data from PDF metadata, and at line [0m[1;36m182[0m[39m uses it as the first [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39margument to ProcessBuilder [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe executable path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, creating a critical OS command [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minjection vulnerability.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Core Fix Strategy[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mImplement a validation method that will be called before any tesseract path is [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mused. The validation must:[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Validate path structure**: Check for shell metacharacters and command [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minjection patterns[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Verify executable existence**: Ensure the file exists and is executable[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Handle relative vs. absolute paths appropriately**: Allow simple executable [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnames [0m[1;39m([0m[39mPATH lookup[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and absolute paths[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Preserve existing functionality**: Maintain the metadata override feature but [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min a secure manner[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Implementation Steps[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### Step [0m[1;36m3.1[0m[39m: Create a new private validation method in OCRStreamEngine[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAdd a new method `[0m[1;35mvalidateTesseractPath[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` that performs comprehensive [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidation:[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprivate String [0m[1;35mvalidateTesseractPath[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath == null || [0m[1;35mpath.trim[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.isEmpty[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Tesseract path cannot be null or empty"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    path = [0m[1;35mpath.trim[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Check for shell metacharacters and command injection patterns[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Reject paths containing: ; & | $ ` < > [0m[1;39m([0m[39m [0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m [0m[1;39m[[0m[39m [0m[1;39m][0m[39m \n \r \t * ? ' "[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mpath.matches[0m[1;39m([0m[32m".*[0m[32m[[0m[32m;&|$`<>[0m[32m([0m[32m)[0m[32m{[0m[32m}[0m[32m\\[0m[32m[[0m[32m\\[0m[32m][0m[32m\\n\\r\\t*?'\"[0m[32m][0m[32m.*"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Invalid tesseract path: contains prohibited [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mcharacters"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Handle two cases:[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Case [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m: Simple executable name [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m[32m"tesseract"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - will use PATH lookup[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Case [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m: Absolute path [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m[32m"/usr/bin/tesseract"[0m[1;39m)[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mpath.contains[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"/"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;35mpath.contains[0m[1;39m([0m[39m"\\"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Contains path separators - treat as absolute/relative path[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        Path tesseractPath = [0m[1;35mPaths.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Normalize to prevent directory traversal[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        tesseractPath = [0m[1;35mtesseractPath.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Verify the file exists and is executable[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mFiles.isExecutable[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtesseractPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Tesseract executable not found or not [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mexecutable: "[0m[39m + tesseractPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        return [0m[1;35mtesseractPath.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Simple name without path separators - allow for PATH lookup[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Additional validation: ensure it's a reasonable executable name[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mpath.matches[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"[0m[32m[[0m[32ma-zA-Z0-9_.-[0m[32m][0m[32m+"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Invalid tesseract executable name: "[0m[39m + path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        return path;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### Step [0m[1;36m3.2[0m[39m: Modify `[0m[1;35mrunTesseract[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method to validate metadata[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mUpdate the `[0m[1;35mrunTesseract[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method at lines [0m[1;36m157[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m167[0m[39m to validate the path after [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mretrieval:[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprivate String [0m[1;35mrunTesseract[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath image[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException [0m[1;39m{[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    String actualTessPath = [0m[1;35mpdDocument.getDocumentInformation[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35m.getCustomMetadataValue[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTESSERACT_PATH_KEY[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mactualTessPath == null || [0m[1;35mactualTessPath.isEmpty[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        actualTessPath = tesseractPath;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m SECURITY FIX: Validate tesseract path before use[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    actualTessPath = [0m[1;35mvalidateTesseractPath[0m[1;39m([0m[39mactualTessPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    Path txt = [0m[1;35mPaths.get[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mimage.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mdoOCR[0m[1;39m([0m[39mactualTessPath, image, txt[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return [0m[1;35mextractContent[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtxt[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### Step [0m[1;36m3.3[0m[39m: Modify `[0m[1;35msetTesseractPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method to validate programmatic input[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mUpdate the setter method at lines [0m[1;36m58[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m60[0m[39m to validate programmatically set paths:[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpublic void [0m[1;35msetTesseractPath[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString tesseractPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    try [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        this.tesseractPath = [0m[1;35mvalidateTesseractPath[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtesseractPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mIOException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        throw new [0m[1;35mIllegalArgumentException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Invalid tesseract path: "[0m[39m + [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtesseractPath, e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m#### Step [0m[1;36m3.4[0m[39m: No changes needed to `[0m[1;35mdoOCR[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe `[0m[1;35mdoOCR[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method at lines [0m[1;36m178[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m197[0m[39m already receives the tesseract path as a [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparameter. Since validation happens before calling this method, no changes are [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mneeded here. The method will receive validated, safe paths.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Rationale and Justification[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Why this is the optimal approach:**[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Defense in Depth**: Validates at both entry points [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmetadata and programmatic [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msetter[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Preserves Functionality**: Maintains the metadata override feature that tests [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpect [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtestOverride[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Follows Existing Patterns**: Uses `[0m[1;35mFiles.isExecutable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` validation already [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdemonstrated in test code[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Minimal Changes**: Only modifies OCRStreamEngine class, no changes to metadata[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAPIs or external dependencies[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Clear Error Messages**: Provides specific feedback when validation fails[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**How it preserves existing logic:**[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **PATH Lookup**: Still allows simple names like [0m[32m"tesseract"[0m[39m for system PATH [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresolution[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Absolute Paths**: Still supports absolute paths like [0m[32m"/usr/bin/tesseract"[0m[39m [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mafter validation[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Metadata Override**: Preserves the feature where PDF metadata overrides [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprogrammatic settings[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Backward Compatibility**: Legitimate configurations continue to work; only [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmalicious inputs are rejected[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**How it addresses the security issue:**[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Blocks Command Injection**: Shell metacharacters are rejected before reaching [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mProcessBuilder[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Prevents Arbitrary Execution**: Only validates, executable files can be used[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Stops Traversal Attacks**: Path normalization prevents directory traversal[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Validates Both Sources**: Checks both metadata and programmatic inputs[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Potential side effects and mitigations:**[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Side Effect**: PDFs with invalid tesseract paths will fail with IOException[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: This is correct behavior - better to fail securely than [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexecute arbitrary commands[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Side Effect**: Relative paths [0m[1;39m([0m[39mexcept simple names[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will be rejected[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: Relative paths are converted to absolute paths via [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mtoAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, then validated[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Side Effect**: Paths with special characters [0m[1;39m([0m[39meven legitimate ones[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m might be [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrejected[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: The regex allows common path characters; truly needed special [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcharacters can be added carefully[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Side Effect**: Performance overhead from validation[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: Minimal - validation happens once per document, not per page[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Similar patterns in the codebase:**[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe test code [0m[1;39m([0m[39mTestOCR.java lines [0m[1;36m21[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m25[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m55[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m already demonstrates proper [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexecutable validation using `[0m[1;35mFiles.isExecutable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. This fix aligns the production [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode with the security practices already present in the test suite.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. Testing Considerations[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix maintains compatibility with existing tests:[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;35mtestBasic[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`: Uses absolute paths validated by the new logic[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;35mtestOverride[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`: PDF metadata override still works, now with validation[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fix properly handles:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Valid absolute paths: `[0m[35m/usr/bin/[0m[95mtesseract[0m[39m` ✓[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Valid simple names: `tesseract` ✓[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Malicious injections: `tesseract; rm -rf [0m[35m/[0m[39m` ✗[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Non-existent files: `[0m[35m/tmp/[0m[95mfake[0m[39m` ✗[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Non-executable files: `[0m[35m/etc/[0m[95mpasswd[0m[39m` ✗[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mduring the OCR processing flow. A patch was attempted that added validation to the [0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnumber in the stack trace [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m224[0m[39m vs [0m[1;36m190[0m[39m in doOCR method[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is an OS Command Injection vulnerability detected during fuzzing.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe security exception indicates that OS commands are being executed with [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattacker-controlled data, which could lead to remote code execution. The [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerability is triggered through the following call chain:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. `[0m[1;35mOCRStreamEngine.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is called [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m71[0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Which calls `[0m[1;35mOCRStreamEngine.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39moverloaded version at line [0m[1;36m88[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mOCRStreamEngine.doOCR[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhere [0m[1;35mProcessBuilder.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is called[0m[1;39m)[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe security scanner detected an OS Command Injection vulnerability, indicating [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat attacker-controlled data is being passed to OS command execution without [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproper validation. The stack trace shows this occurs when [0m[1;35mProcessBuilder.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvoked from the [0m[1;35mdoOCR[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m method.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Patch Attempt Description[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch introduced a `[0m[1;35mvalidateTesseractPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method to sanitize the tesseract [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpath before executing commands. The patch makes the following changes:[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Modified `[0m[1;35msetTesseractPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method to validate the path through [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mvalidateTesseractPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and throw `IllegalArgumentException` on invalid paths.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Added a call to `[0m[1;35mvalidateTesseractPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in the `[0m[1;35mrunTesseract[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method before [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexecuting the command [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m168[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Introduced a new private method `[0m[1;35mvalidateTesseractPath[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` that [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mperforms the following validations:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Checks if the path is null or empty[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Trims the path string[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Checks for prohibited shell metacharacters using regex: [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`.*[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m;&|$`<>[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m{[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m\\[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m\\[0m[1;39m][0m[39m\\n\\r\\t*?'\"[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.*`[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If the path contains [0m[32m"/"[0m[39m or "\" [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi.e., it's a full path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Converts to absolute and normalized Path[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Verifies the file is executable[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Returns the normalized path[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If the path is just a command name [0m[1;39m([0m[39mno path separators[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Validates it contains only alphanumeric characters, underscores, dots, and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhyphens[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Returns the path as-is [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfor PATH lookup[0m[1;39m)[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is an **OS Command Injection** vulnerability reported by a fuzzer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecurity check [0m[1;39m([0m[39mJazzer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The stack trace indicates:[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. The exception originates from [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mcom.code_intelligence.jazzer.sanitizers.OsCommandInjection.processImplStartHook[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. The vulnerability is triggered during the execution of an OS command in [0m         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mOCRStreamEngine.runTesseract[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m165[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mOCRStreamEngine.processPage[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m150[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mOCRStreamEngine.processPages[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m140[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mOCRStreamEngine.writeText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m129[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mOCRStreamEngine.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at lines [0m[1;36m88[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m71[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe issue is classified as **OS Command Injection**, which is a critical security [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerability where attacker-controlled data is passed to OS command execution [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout proper validation.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Patch Analysis[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch attempt introduces input validation for the Tesseract path through a new [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethod `[0m[1;35mvalidateTesseractPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. The patch:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Modified `[0m[1;35msetTesseractPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m58[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m64[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Wraps the path assignment with validation[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Catches IOException and throws IllegalArgumentException[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Added validation in `[0m[1;35mrunTesseract[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m168[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Validates the actual tesseract path before use[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **New `[0m[1;35mvalidateTesseractPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m174[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m199[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Checks for null or empty paths[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Validates against shell metacharacters using regex: [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`.*[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m;&|$`<>[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m{[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m\\[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m\\[0m[1;39m][0m[39m\\n\\r\\t*?'\"[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.*`[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - For paths with directory separators, validates:[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Normalizes the path[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Checks if the file is executable[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - For bare executables [0m[1;39m([0m[39mno path separators[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, validates against a whitelist: [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[39ma-zA-Z0-9_.-[0m[1;39m][0m[39m+`[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Result After Patch[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe OS Command Injection vulnerability **still persists** after applying the patch.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe stack trace shows:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Same `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: OS Command Injection` exception[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The error still occurs at `[0m[1;35mProcessBuilder.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` when calling `[0m[1;35mdoOCR[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m224[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mversus line [0m[1;36m190[0m[39m in the original[0m[1;39m)[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The stack trace is nearly identical to the original, just with slightly different[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline numbers[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue reveals an **OS Command Injection vulnerability** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mclassified as [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma critical security issue[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in the Apache PDFBox OCR component. The vulnerability is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdetected by Jazzer's sanitizer during fuzz testing.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Key observations:**[0m                                                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating that attacker-controlled data is being used in OS command execution[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. The stack trace shows the vulnerability occurs in the OCR processing pipeline:[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mOCRStreamEngine.doOCR[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m190[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mOCRStreamEngine.runTesseract[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at line [0m[1;36m165[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Called through a chain starting from `[0m[1;35mOCRStreamEngine.getText[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. The issue is triggered through `[0m[1;35mProcessBuilder.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, which is used to [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexecute external OS commands[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. The fuzzer identifies this as an [0m[32m"OS Command Injection"[0m[39m vulnerability - a [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcritical security issue where attacker-controlled data could lead to remote code [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexecution[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Patch Attempt[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch attempts to address the OS command injection vulnerability by introducing[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minput validation for the tesseract executable path. Key changes include:[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Modified `setTesseractPath` method** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m56[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m64[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Wrapped the assignment with a try-catch block[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added validation through a new `[0m[1;35mvalidateTesseractPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Throws `IllegalArgumentException` if validation fails[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Updated `runTesseract` method** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m168[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added validation of `actualTessPath` before using it in the command[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Added `validateTesseractPath` method** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m174[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m200[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Checks for null or empty paths[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Uses regex to detect shell metacharacters: `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m;&|$`<>[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m{[0m[1;39m}[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m\\n\\r\\t*?'"[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - For paths containing `[0m[35m/[0m[39m` or `\\`:[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Converts to absolute normalized path[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Verifies the file is executable[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - For simple executable names [0m[1;39m([0m[39mno path separators[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Validates against allowed characters: `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39ma-zA-Z0-9_.-[0m[1;39m][0m[39m+`[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Result Analysis[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe error persists after applying the patch. Key observations:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Same vulnerability triggered**: The OS Command Injection detection still fires[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat the same logical point [0m[1;39m([0m[39mProcessBuilder.start[0m[1;39m)[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Stack trace changes**: [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Before: `[0m[1;35mdoOCR[0m[1;39m([0m[39mOCRStreamEngine.jav[0m[1;92ma:190[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After: `[0m[1;35mdoOCR[0m[1;39m([0m[39mOCRStreamEngine.jav[0m[1;92ma:224[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This indicates the validation code was added but the vulnerable call still [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexecutes[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Different DEDUP_TOKEN**: Changed from `af83c7db521bbc07` to [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`fb620e333dcce929`, suggesting the crash signature differs slightly[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Validation bypassed**: The patch's validation logic is either:[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Not being invoked in the code path that leads to the vulnerability[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Being invoked but still allowing malicious input through[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Throwing an exception that is caught and handled somewhere, allowing execution[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto continue[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas Requiring Investigation[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **The `doOCR` method** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m224[0m[39m in patched version[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This is where `[0m[1;35mProcessBuilder.start[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is ultimately called[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Need to examine how the tesseract path is used in command construction[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - May need to validate not just the path but also how it's passed to [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mProcessBuilder[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Command construction logic**:[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How are command-line arguments assembled?[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Are there other user-controlled inputs besides the tesseract path?[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Are arguments properly escaped or quoted?[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Alternative code paths**:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The validation is added to `runTesseract` and `setTesseractPath`[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Are there other methods that call `doOCR` directly without validation?[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Could `doOCR` be invoked through a different path?[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **ProcessBuilder usage**:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Need to review the exact ProcessBuilder configuration in `doOCR`[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Should verify if array-based command construction is used vs. string [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconcatenation[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Input sources**:[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - What other parameters can be influenced by attacker-controlled data?[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Are there language settings, output paths, or other options that feed into the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcommand?[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Exception handling**:[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Is the IOException from validation being caught somewhere?[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Could a try-catch block be allowing the code to fall through to the vulnerable[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcall?[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Root Cause Confirmation[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability exists in the `[0m[1;35mrunTesseract[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m157[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m167[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Line [0m[1;36m158[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m159[0m[39m**: Retrieves tesseract path from PDF document metadata [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mcompletely attacker-controlled[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Line [0m[1;36m160[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m162[0m[39m**: Falls back to `tesseractPath` field only if metadata is [0m       [2m                [0m
